ratings.question_text: What is your overall assessment of this course?

narratives.question_text: How would you summarize AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 for a fellow student? Would you recommend AFAM 505 01/AMST 643 01 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: I would recommend the course to any student interested in open debate, constructive criticism and a curiosity for new methodological approaches. l

narratives.question_text: How did this course deepen your knowledge of your discipline/profession? To what extent did this course contribute to your dissertation/research?
comments: See my answers above. The course contributed to my overall understanding of art history by opening a new field of research for me that will have to be integrated into my main interest in the theory of the image. Therefore, I expect this course to have a long lasting impact on my thinking and my own research projects, even though they are not directly connected to medieval sculpture.
